    "# KRITIS\u2013Philippines: Typhoon \u00d7 Grid Disruption Screening\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objective\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook implements a first-pass **topological screening model** of typhoon-induced grid disruption in the Philippines.\n",
    "\n",
    "Historical typhoon track points from **IBTrACS** are translated into stylized line hazards on a **PyPSA-PH** transmission network. Lines exceeding a hazard threshold are assumed to fail. Buses that are no longer connected to any generator-containing network component are treated as **unserved**.\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook includes two consequence logics:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **v4b**: nearest-bus population attribution + binary generator-presence service rule\n",
    "- **v5r**: nearest-bus population attribution + **capacity-aware relative adequacy** service rule\n",
    "\n",
    "## Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a **comparative stress-test on a common benchmark network**, not a reconstruction of the exact historical infrastructure in each storm year.\n",
    "\n",
    "Key simplifications:\n",
    "- the transmission network is treated as static\n",
    "- population is fixed to one contemporary raster\n",
    "- line hazard is based on sampled points along each transmission line\n",
    "- failure is threshold-based, not probabilistic\n",
    "- service is based on graph connectivity, not electrical load flow\n",
    "- generation adequacy is represented only by installed generator capacity relative to a population proxy\n",
    "\n",
    "## Canonical model choice\n",
    "\n",
    "The notebook retains **v4b** for benchmarking, but the preferred specification is:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **v5r**\n",
    "- stylized wind-field hazard\n",
    "- unique nearest-bus population assignment\n",
    "- capacity-aware **relative adequacy** service screening\n"
   ]
